FBIS3-49328 "dreeu006_i_94019" FBIS-EEU-94-006 Document Type:Daily Report 10 Jan 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA Serbs Prevent Electricity Repairs AU1001100494 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in Serbo-Croatian 0900 GMT 10 Jan 94 AU1001100494 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network Language: Serbo-Croatian Article Type:BFN [Text] Ten megawatts of electricity are reaching Sarajevo today. This is enough only for basic humanitarian needs. The Serbian side still has not given its approval for beginning repairs on the Reljevo-[name indistinct] long distance transmission line, so it is uncertain when citizens will be supplied with electricity. The waterworks information service informs that they are still having problems and that the amount of water supplied to the city is still inadequate. The pumping system [words indistinct]. Nevertheless, the supply of water to Sarajevo is improving. Water is being supplied every day or every other day. No water is coming in from the Jahorina springs and there is no possibility of alternately supplying water in a part of the supply zone of (?Hamdina Carina). The Pivara spring is operational and only the water from this spring is chlorinated. Today the Sarajevo bakery will supply bread to the majority of communes in the city and to all priority consumers. Tomorrow's production is uncertain owing to lack of [words indistinct].
